  "texts": [
    "(A.3)):B del = B[W E (B tens + B lens + B noise) ⋆ β] ≈ B[W E (B tens + B lens + B noise) ⋆ (β ϕ + β noise)] ≈ B[W E B tens ⋆ β] + B[W E B lens ⋆ β ϕ] + B[W E B lens ⋆ β noise] + B[W E B noise ⋆ β] -W E B lens = (W E)B tens + B del S + B del N + (W E)B noise.",
    "(2.27)Here, B[B ⋆ ϕ] represents the delensing operation of lensing B mode with ϕ to obtain the delensed B-modes.",
    "We have checked that the inverse-lensing procedure have negligible effect on the tensor B-mode, so the first brace is almost equal to the filtered input tensor B-mode with the change accounted for by B del S (see Appendix D).",
    "B del S includes the delensed B signal (the second brace), which is the desired output and arises from the method itself, therefore exists even under noiseless observation.",
    "While the last brace contains both the intrinsic noise (W E)B noise and the noise part B del N introduced by the delensing procedure."
